<h2 id="places-that-did-not-fit-into-the-previous-categories-but-are-still-worth-trying">Places that did not fit into the previous categories but are still worth trying</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/HfN8hgJQsGFeX5mV6">Ai Tre Scalini</a>
It is within walking distance of the Colosseum, on a very nice street with a great atmosphere. If you catch a sunny day, it is another good place to eat outside. It has a small terrace. It is usually crowded, so if you want to visit this one, try going earlier or later than the usual lunch time.</li>
  <li><a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/FbK3fBmUWbstuBEV9">Trapizzino</a>
This is yet another version of pizza. It is not a traditional pizza, but it is still very good and perfect to take away. There are multiple locations. There is one close to <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/JsEZfJdiCPm1qhMD6">Ponte Sisto</a> and <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/GLyS9FNtjhmxTsbC8">Piazza Trilussa</a>.</li>
